  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-surface-dim bg-dots">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="section-label text-accent mb-4">Conveyor Types</div>
      <h1 class="font-display text-5xl sm:text-6xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide uppercase leading-tight mb-8">
        Belt Conveyors: Types, Materials &#x26; Selection Guide
      </h1>
      <div class="text-xl text-ink-muted leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
        <p>A belt conveyor uses a continuous loop of flexible material stretched between pulleys to transport products. Unlike <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">roller conveyors</a> that require flat-bottomed loads, belt conveyors handle products of any shape: bags, pouches, irregular items, small parts, and loose bulk materials. Belt types range from general-purpose flat belts to specialized cleated, modular plastic, and wire mesh designs for specific applications.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Belt Type Navigation -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-surface" aria-labelledby="subtypes-heading">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="section-label text-accent mb-4">Belt Conveyor Types</div>
