  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface-dim" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 id="faq-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide mb-10">
        Frequently Asked <span class="text-accent">Questions</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8" open>
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is a belt conveyor?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>A belt conveyor uses a continuous loop of material (the belt) stretched between two or more pulleys to transport products. The belt wraps around a head pulley (driven) and a tail pulley (idler), with the top surface carrying products and the bottom returning empty. Belt conveyors handle products of any shape, size, or bottom condition, including bags, pouches, and irregular shapes that <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">roller conveyors</a> cannot transport.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What are the different types of conveyor belts?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Common conveyor belt types include: <a href="/conveyor-types/flat-belt-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">flat belt</a> (smooth surface for general transport), <a href="/conveyor-types/cleated-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">cleated belt</a> (raised flights for inclines), <a href="/conveyor-types/modular-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">modular plastic belt</a> (interlocking modules for food and washdown), timing/positive drive belt (toothed for precise positioning), <a href="/conveyor-types/wire-mesh-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">wire mesh belt</a> (open weave for high temperatures), and specialty belts (vacuum, magnetic, rough-top).</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is the difference between a belt conveyor and a roller conveyor?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Belt conveyors use a continuous belt surface and can transport products of any shape or bottom condition. <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Roller conveyors</a> use cylindrical rollers and require flat, rigid product bottoms spanning at least 3 rollers. Belt conveyors excel at <a href="/conveyor-types/incline-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">inclines</a>, handling bags and pouches, and transporting small items. Roller conveyors offer easier zone control, <a href="/conveyor-types/accumulation-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">accumulation</a>, and lower friction for heavy flat-bottomed loads.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What belt conveyor is best for food applications?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p><a href="/conveyor-types/modular-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Modular plastic belt conveyors</a> are preferred for <a href="/industries/food-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">food and beverage applications</a> because they are easy to clean, resistant to water and chemicals, available in FDA-compliant materials, and suitable for <a href="/industries/food-conveyors/sanitary/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">washdown environments</a>. For dry food, FDA-compliant PU flat belts are also common. <a href="/conveyor-types/wire-mesh-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Wire mesh belts</a> are used for <a href="/industries/food-conveyors/bakery/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">baking</a>, <a href="/industries/food-conveyors/cooling/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">cooling</a>, and freezing.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            How fast can a belt conveyor run?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Belt conveyor speeds typically range from 20 to 400 feet per minute (FPM) depending on the application. Light-duty <a href="/industries/packaging-line-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">packaging conveyors</a> commonly run at 50-150 FPM. High-speed sortation and distribution conveyors may reach 400-600 FPM. Maximum practical speed depends on belt type, product stability, and the ability to load and unload at the conveyor ends. <a href="/conveyor-types/incline-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Incline conveyors</a> run slower to prevent product slippage.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

